Questions on the banking ombudsman
scheme typically come in a few flavors.

00:02:20.655 --> 00:02:25.605
About 30% of questions are definition
purpose-based, asking about the

00:02:25.605 --> 00:02:30.225
main objective, who introduced
it, or the act it operates under.

00:02:30.640 --> 00:02:35.800
Then about 25% are jurisdiction
scope based questions, which test you

00:02:35.920 --> 00:02:40.150
on, what complaints are covered, or
which banks fall under the scheme.

00:02:40.570 --> 00:02:45.250
Roughly 20% are process, procedure
based questions, focusing on time

00:02:45.250 --> 00:02:49.360
limits for filing complaints or
the maximum compensation amount.

00:02:49.960 --> 00:02:54.460
Around 15% are about key provisions,
amendments, looking at specific

00:02:54.460 --> 00:02:56.230
clauses or recent changes.

00:02:56.600 --> 00:03:00.710
And the final 10% are role
function based questions, which

00:03:00.710 --> 00:03:02.810
ask about the ombudsman's powers.

00:03:03.644 --> 00:03:04.994
Formulas and tricks.

00:03:05.295 --> 00:03:08.954
While there are no magical
formulas, here are the key facts

00:03:08.954 --> 00:03:10.785
you must tattoo onto your brain.

00:03:11.204 --> 00:03:14.415
The RBI introduced and
operates the scheme.

00:03:14.774 --> 00:03:20.054
The legal basis is Section 35 A of
the Banking Regulation Act 1949.

00:03:21.190 --> 00:03:24.220
The bank gets a 30 day
time limit to respond.

00:03:24.370 --> 00:03:29.560
Before you can approach the ombudsman,
you have one year plus 30 days from

00:03:29.560 --> 00:03:31.540
the issue date to file your complaint.

00:03:31.960 --> 00:03:37.270
The maximum compensation for direct
loss is a cool 20 lack while for mental

00:03:37.270 --> 00:03:39.790
agony and harassment, it is one lack.

00:03:40.240 --> 00:03:44.230
The methods of resolution are
either conciliation or an award.

00:03:44.620 --> 00:03:46.300
If you are still not satisfied.

00:03:46.450 --> 00:03:50.110
The appellate authority is a
deputy governor of the RBI.

00:03:50.525 --> 00:03:53.435
The current scheme is called
the Integrated Scheme,

00:03:53.525 --> 00:03:55.715
which was launched in 2021.

00:03:56.579 --> 00:03:59.609
Methods of solving to
grasp its functioning.

00:03:59.700 --> 00:04:02.130
Just follow this step-by-step approach.

00:04:02.399 --> 00:04:07.530
First, you must understand the grievance
and identify the nature of your complaint.

00:04:07.829 --> 00:04:12.149
Second, remember the initial
bank approach as you must contact

00:04:12.149 --> 00:04:13.920
your bank first for resolution.

00:04:14.310 --> 00:04:18.510
Third note, the mandatory time
limit for bank, which is that 30 day

00:04:18.510 --> 00:04:20.370
waiting period for their response.

00:04:20.709 --> 00:04:25.150
Fourth, understand the Ombudsman's
role as an independent decision maker.

00:04:25.480 --> 00:04:29.560
Fifth, know the complaint filing
method and its specific timeframe.

00:04:29.800 --> 00:04:33.969
Sixth, be aware that the
resolution process can be a mutual

00:04:33.969 --> 00:04:35.890
agreement or a formal award.

00:04:36.250 --> 00:04:40.540
Lastly, recognize the appeal mechanism,
knowing there is a provision to

00:04:40.540 --> 00:04:42.400
appeal the Ombudsman's decision.

