00:05:34.245 --> 00:05:36.195
Common mistakes and misconceptions.

00:05:36.465 --> 00:05:38.295
Let's clear up some common myths.

00:05:38.505 --> 00:05:42.825
First mistake believing the ombudsman
is only for public sector banks.

00:05:42.885 --> 00:05:47.655
Wrong the scheme covers all scheduled
commercial banks, regional rural banks,

00:05:47.655 --> 00:05:49.875
and scheduled primary cooperative banks.

00:05:50.145 --> 00:05:51.075
Second mistake.

00:05:51.225 --> 00:05:53.745
Thinking you can directly
approach the ombudsman.

00:05:53.895 --> 00:05:54.795
No, you cannot.

00:05:54.975 --> 00:05:58.785
It is mandatory to complain to
the bank first and wait 30 days.

00:05:59.205 --> 00:06:02.025
Third mistake, confusing
the compensation amounts.

00:06:02.025 --> 00:06:07.364
Remember it is 20 lack for direct loss,
but only one lack for mental harassment.

00:06:07.664 --> 00:06:08.565
Fourth mistake.

00:06:08.655 --> 00:06:13.575
Assuming all banking issues are covered,
Nope, only specific services are covered.

00:06:13.664 --> 00:06:15.674
Commercial decisions are excluded.

00:06:15.974 --> 00:06:20.655
Fifth mistake believing the ombudsman's
decision is final Correction, there

00:06:20.655 --> 00:06:25.034
is an upper authority, the deputy
governor of RBI where you can appeal.

